Iwamoto Mari (巖本 真理, 19 January 1926―11 May 1979) was a Japanese violinist.
From 1946 to 1949, she was a professor at the Tokyo Academy of Music, resigning the post in 1949 in order to spend a year in the USA.
She stayed there in a year and half, and took lesson of George Enescu in Chicago, and Louis Persinger in New York at The Juilliard School.
